reviews.review_text: Best show of the run. This is the strongest show of the three night Oakland run, with the band on better form than the previous night, and Jerry especially playing somewhat better. The first set has some shakey moments, but the second set gets off to a fine start with a rocking Victim (gotta love the drum intro) followed by a VERY soulful Speedway Boogie. Sound quality on this one is perhaps not quite as good as the 1st or 3rd nights but it certainly manages to capture the atmosphere in the building. While this show is still a '95, it is worth downloading just for the New Speedway Boogie, which will have the hairs standing on the back of your neck.

No easy answers As another reviewer said, the fourteen minute New Speedway Boogie is easily the highlight of what is otherwise a lackluster show. This audience recording is boomy - a fairly typical result for Oakland Arena AUDs. This was my last GD show and the 20th that I attended in the post-Brent era, and it was probably the least inspired show that I ever saw. Although I was there, I still don't plan to download this one. New Speedway was played 30 times since its breakout on 2/19/91; there are many other modern versions that beat this one.

fat  balloon nails it Nothing spectacular indeed. Was not at or heard the first night, but I understand that is even worse. I was at this show and couldn't really rememeber anything of interest musically. Pass on this one.

interesting how they.... I was there too,  All three nights.  Even while I was there, I was very sad about how they played the first night, then the second night first set, I am sad to say I thought it was god-freakin-awful.  And then they did that thing they sometimes did in the late-later days..... out of *nowhere* they remembered how to play, REALLY play.  The Victim is really amazing and I would love to know about a Speedway better than this one.  The recording doesn't do it justice but if you really listen you can hear the nuances that make it spectacular.  I loved the whole second set.  Still do!  The third night was also really disappointing... but this second set is amazing.  I hope someone puts up a good recording someday, if only of this part of the run.  :-)  4 stars for the stellar second, and so this show gets some attention... hoping for a better recording!
wish it didn't  sound so crappy my 100th show. and I get cheezy answers.
Wait for the Upgrade David Gans just played this date on the GRATEFUL DEAD Hour.  A decent SBD should be here soon as is often the case with his material...

Dont listen its all part of the same artistry everything they ever did is 100% I only went to one show in 86' but i tell you ive been hooked ever since! You critics have your opinion this is mine. 
There never was a bad dead show, not the first one not the last. Wish i had had your tickets!!!
